Motoring news and views from the usual team. Jeremy Clarkson and James May
invade Greenham Common airbase to ask if the Communists ever made a good car.
Out on the test track, Richard Hammond goes crazy in the Veritas, a German
sports car, and Jeremy conducts an almost ridiculously thorough road test of
the new Ford Fiesta. Plus, London mayor Boris Johnson is the Star in a
Reasonably Priced Car.
